higher educational settings, and leaders, teachers or coaches in physical education and physical activity programs. >> Learn more about the PhD in Educational Psychology - Concentration in Sport Pedagogy >> See Educational Psychology Graduate Admissions for application procedures For questions on specific course requirements of this program, potential students may also contact the program coordinator, Dr. Tao Zhang (Tao.Zhang@unt.edu). Please contact the program coordinator prior to applying to ask about program capacity. AttachmentSize PHD-Sport-Pedagogy-Degree-Plan.docx24.97 KB PHD-Sport Pedagogy-78 Hour Degree-Plan.docx25.6 KB Back to Masters and Doctoral Programs Department of Educational Psychology Contact Information College of Education Matthews Hall, Room 214 1300 West Highland Street Denton, TX 76203 Contact the College of Education Email Us For technical problems with this web site, contact COEWeb@unt.edu.     UNT System UNT System UNT Dallas Campus UNT Health Science Center Universities Center at Dallas Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy Statement | Web Accessibility Policy | State of Texas Online Go to Secure Login Page 